  "prompt": "What is the PAN number of the Punjab National Bank (PNB)?",
  "response": "The PAN (Permanent Account Number) is a unique identifier issued by the Indian Income Tax Department to individuals and entities for tax purposes. The PAN for any bank, including Punjab National Bank (PNB), can vary by branch or region. Generally, banks do not publicly share their PAN numbers for security and privacy reasons. \n\nIf you need the PAN number for a specific branch of Punjab National Bank for official purposes, it is best to contact the bank directly or visit their official website for assistance.",
